title: Medical Microbiology by Kayser
description:
Medical Microbiology comprises and integrates the fields of immunology,
bacteriology, virology, mycology, and parasitology.

The objective of this textbook of medical microbiology is to instill a broadbased
knowledge of the etiologic organisms causing disease and the pathogenetic
mechanisms leading to clinically manifest infections into its users.

Kayser, 2005.
